<title>USA: Platinum to take $40 mln-$45 mln charge.</title>
<headline>Platinum to take $40 mln-$45 mln charge.</headline>
<dateline>OAKBROOK TERRACE, Ill. 1997-05-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Platinum Technology Inc said Thursday it expects to take a $40 million to $45 million charge in the second quarter as it cuts aobut 400 jobs from its workforce.  </p>
<p>The company said it expects to see annual expenses cut by about $40 million as it completes the assimilation of about 40 acquisitions made over the past two years.</p>
<p>The job cuts will come from consolidating sales, marketing, business development, and product development operations.</p>
<p>The announcement is in line with Platinum's previously stated commitments to earnings growth objectives, the system software company said.</p>
<p>Platinum shares closed up 1/2 at 12-1/2 Thursday.</p>
<p>((Chicago newsdesk, 312-408-8787))</p>
